The paper studies a non-linear dynamical system that models opinion formation, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems. Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with convergence analysis, which is a common topic in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of polynomial time bounds suggests a connection to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the system being studied is a popular one in the field, which could indicate a connection to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
